commands_raw:
"At last we meet, Quaestor."
?>"Lady Thirla Merina. I trust you know why you are here." -> entry 1
name: start

commands_raw:
Thirla Merina smiles. A practiced, cold smile that betrays nothing behind it.
"That unpleasantness? I assure thee, me and mine are untouched by esoterica. Ill words brought to thine ears by jealousness and envy."
?> "The truth will come out, whatever it may be." -> questions
name: entry 1

commands_raw:
?>"Lady Merina. Tell me about yourself." -> q1a1
?>"Question number two" -> q2a1
name: questions

commands_raw:
"Oh, Quaestor, doth thine parchments not detail the legacy of mine noble house in sufficient majesty?"
?>"Humor me." -> q1a2
name: q1a1

commands_raw:
"As thy wish. I am the daughter and heir of Lord Agustine Merina, Landgrave and Lord of Astra Nova, loyal servant of Grand Duchess Jillian Mercuno. Our line is old as the First Empire."
?>"..." -> q1a3
name: q1a2

commands_raw:
The noblewoman eyes you closely. Her emerald eye seems to sparkle in the darkness of the room like a corona in the darkness of space. Her gaze is that of a bird of prey instead of a prisoner being interrogated.
?>"..." -> q1a4
name: q1a3

commands_raw:
"Deeds of our line number countless as the stars, accolades upon accolades are heaped at our feet. Doth this not answer thy inquiry? I hold the fate of millions in mine grasp, mine wealth and influence matchless as the brightness of sun to a candle."
?>"I have other questions" -> questions
name: q1a4
